my dog has gone i had to have my dog put down on friday aug i really really do miss her i feel really lost i feel like crying all the time some people would say dont be silly its only a dog maybe but she was my dog she was really good to me she was my baby she was years old she was having fits and had internal problems i stayed with her untill she had gone i had her sitting on my lap while the vet done it i was cuddling her i couldnt leave her alone i keep thinking wheres holly spare food left on plates i keep going to say give this to holly then i remember shes not here anymorefriday morning i gave her lots of yummy food i gave her fresh cooked sausages sweets chocolate icepoles anything i had that she liked she had i loved that dog just as much as i love my kids i know im being stupid but i had her since she was a puppy i just dont know what to do with myself i miss her hi jman my dog only had that food friday morning cause she was being put down in the afternoon i didnt feed her on that food when she was alive just on friday before she had to go i have a lot of empathy for you i am a pet ownerof a shih tzu poo cats rats parakeets and a cockatiel i can't have kids so my pets help to fill the void i can tell how much holly meant to you you bond with your pets on a level that is completely different than that of a human they give you unconditional love no matter what we have how we look or how much money we make they are there for you regardless all they ask for is some food and attention in return you couldn't find a more devoted friend and companion i will include a poem that is pretty well known and might offer you some comfort in your time of grief when you are ready think about getting a new dog it doesn't need to be the same breed or anything unless that is what you want you could save a life by rescuing a dog from a shelter that hasn't ever known the love that you gave holly you are in my thoughts maybe before you feel ready to adopt a dog you could visit a local animal shelter or rescue organization just volunteer and spend some time giving attention to a dog that doesn't have anyone else it might help lessen your pain it does get better doesn't ever go away but the pain will ease a bit each day rainbow bridge just this side of heaven is a place called rainbow bridge when an animal dies that has been especially close to someone here that pet goes to rainbow bridge there are meadows and hills for all of our special friends so they can run and play together there is plenty of food water and sunshine and our friends are warm and comfortable all the animals who had been ill and old are restored to health and vigor those who were hurt or maimed are made whole and strong again just as we remember them in our dreams of days and times gone by the animals are happy and content except for one small thing they each miss someone very special to them who had to be left behind they all run and play together but the day comes when one suddenly stops and looks into the distance his bright eyes are intent his eager body quivers suddenly he begins to run from the group flying over the green grass his legs carrying him faster and faster you have been spotted and when you and your special friend finally meet you cling together in joyous reunion never to be parted again the happy kisses rain upon your face your hands again caress the beloved head and you look once more into the trusting eyes of your pet so long gone from your life but never absent from your heart then you cross rainbow bridge together Cat The Amber Spyglass Kodocha Dog Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Pitaten Dog training Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Care Bears W.I.T.C.H. 2000 Australian Grand Prix EastEnders Guinea pig Salad Fingers Hamster Pet skunk Cliff Richard Theory of conduct Time Out of Mind AFI 100 Years series Sin City Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Ferret Piccolo Junior Saga Futurama (TV series - season 5) Parsifal The Lovely Bones Phoebe B